  "description": "Issue #11 slice 1 (+review-fix round) release counterpart of debugtools-hub-modern-debug.json: identical frame-for-frame input script (same intro-advance taps, the same repeated SELECT+R hotkey pulse at frames 600-606 and 650-656 reproducing the reviewer's release-and-repress case, and the same follow-up A press at frame 700 that would select the built-in launcher in a debug build) is replayed against a modern release build. In release, FE8_EXPANSION_DEBUGTOOLS_ENABLED is compiled out: DebugTools_TitleHotkeyCheck/OpenHub compile to inert stubs, the hub menu table and the built-in launcher's action body do not exist in the link at all (see docs/debugtools.md), and Title_IDLE's own vanilla A/START handling is never intercepted -- so repeating the hotkey pulse cannot open a hub at all, let alone a second concurrent one. gDebugToolsProbe remains a harmless all-zero BSS struct that is never written. Every probe therefore reads 0x00000000 at every checkpoint -- proving the hotkey (single or repeated) has no effect and the hub/launcher are absent, not merely unreached.",
